item.title: Im extremely new at private servers
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

Download a new server at this link:

http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php?board=49.0

Then download a server and uncompress it. Then you need to download the newest java at this link:

http://192.18.108.205/ECom/EComTicketServlet/BEGINCDDC6234CEA7FEA3D37CE83BD2D44C05/-2147483648/1738929783/1/772394/772106/1738929783/2ts+/westCoastFSEND/jdk-1.5.0_09-oth-JPR/jdk-1.5.0_09-oth-JPR:2/jdk-1_5_0_09-windows-i586-p.exe

Ok now go into your server folder that you now have and right click compile.bat and erase everything that is in it. Then make it look like this:

@echo off COLOR 08 title yourserver compiler "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_09\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java pause

Then save it and exit out of it. Now right click and edit run&compile.bat (unless your server doesnt have it) and erase all thats in it. Put this in its place:

@echo off COLOR 02 title yourserver client "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_09\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java java -Xmx1024m -cp .;./jython.jar;./MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.17-ga-bin.jar server pause

Ok now save it and exit out. Now if u click on the compile.bat it will compile your server and the run&compile will compile the server and then run it (hence the names). I hope this helped you. Enjoy!

~Mod Taharok

item.title: Im extremely new at private servers
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

Here is one of my old posts on this issue:

Ok I hate repeating this so tell this to everyone who has this error and say its for Mod Taharok. Ok so first of all your saving issues are because of no auto saver. The first thing you should do is look in tuts section for an auto-saver for testscape. Next YOU CANT USE ONLY NO-IP TO RUN A SERVER. If you have a router (almost everyone does), then type in the ip address of the router into your address bar. Then log into the router settings. Click on “Advanced”, then click on the side panel “gameing” (this is if your using a DLink router, but if you have somthing else it should be similar). Ok now you have to make a new rule, the name should be your server name. Next the computer IP should be the ACTUAL COMPUTER IP, NOT THE INTERNET IP FOR THAT COMPUTER, THE REAL THING! Next in the Tcp ports to open is supposed to be “43594”. Then click “save settings”. Ok now go to no-ip and your IP address should be there (internet IP this time, not real IP like the one used to log into router or to make rule). Now it should work successfully. If you dont have a router then you probably have to use Hamachi (peer to peer), and I dont like peer to peer so I have no clue how to use it. I hope this helped. Enjoy!

~Mod Taharok
